==English==

===Pronunciation===
rŭb, /rʌb/, /<tt>rVb</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-rub.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌb|-ʌb]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An act of [[rubbing]].
#: ''Give that lamp a good '''rub''' and see if any genies come out''
# a [[difficulty]] or [[problem]]
#: ''Therein lies the '''rub'''.''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[hankaus]]
*Portuguese: [[fricção]] {{f}}
*Turkish: [[ovma]], [[ovalama]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|rub|b|ing}}

# To move one object while maintaining contact with another object over some area.
#: ''I '''rubbed''' the cloth over the glass''.
#: ''The cat '''rubbed''' itself against my leg''.
#: ''I '''rubbed''' my hands together for warmth''.
# To rub something against.
#: ''I '''rubbed''' the glass with the cloth''.
# To rub against something.
#: ''My shoes are beginning to '''rub'''''.

